text.tspan: Make incident halfedge to vo point to vh (in blue)
After this, some faces are two sided
(in pink, for real they have no surface)
Remove loops, i.e. halfedges hn and op (in red, and the pink faces)
hp and on remains (corresponding to the purple edges/halfedges)
hp (resp. on) is modified to have the wedge of halfedge a (resp. b)
Wedges updates work has follow: if multiple wedges are around vo and vh, we try to identify
a feature loop, to update wedges respecting the loop.
In the general case, if vh as two different wedges on both side of h, the first one will be set to all halfedges pointing to vo that have the
same wedge has hp, the second one will be set to the remaining halfedges
